Sentencas: BaSrInFeO5 (BSIF), a new cathode material for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), is designed based on the modification of the Ba2In2O5 proton conductor with Sr and Fe cations.
Titulo: Sr and Fe co-doped Ba2In2O5 as a new proton-conductor-derived cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with the Ba2In2O5 proton conductor tailored with only Fe cations (Ba2InFeO5, BIF), doping Sr can improve the chemical stability and also benefit the formation of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Sr and Fe co-doped Ba2In2O5 as a new proton-conductor-derived cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The proton mobility is also improved with Sr-doping, which is confirmed by first-principles calculations and experimental studies.
Titulo: Sr and Fe co-doped Ba2In2O5 as a new proton-conductor-derived cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An H-SOFC using the BSIF cathode generates a relatively high peak power density of 1192 mW cm-2 at 700 oC, which is superior to many cells in previous reports.
Titulo: Sr and Fe co-doped Ba2In2O5 as a new proton-conductor-derived cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: First-principles calculations find that the cathode oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) energy barrier for BSIF is significantly lower than that for BIF.
Titulo: Sr and Fe co-doped Ba2In2O5 as a new proton-conductor-derived cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Although Ba2In2O5 is less studied, the derived cathode materials can still present decent performance, probably offering new material selections for H-SOFCs.
Titulo: Sr and Fe co-doped Ba2In2O5 as a new proton-conductor-derived cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
